Apple has launched a new iPad Air and a new iPad Mini. The two new models feature a 10.5-inch display and 7.9-inch display, respectively, and offer Wi-Fi or Wi-Fi+Cellular connectivity. Colour options are silver, space grey, or gold. “The all-new iPad Air in an ultra-thin 10.5-inch design, offering the latest innovations including Apple Pencil support and high-end performance at a breakthrough price,” said Apple. This is thanks to the device’s A12 Bionic chip with Apple’s Neural Engine. The new 7.9-inch iPad Mini is a “major upgrade for iPad Mini fans who love a compact, ultra-portable design packed with the latest technology”, added Apple. It also features the company’s A12 Bionic chip. The pricing of the new iPads is as follows: Wi-Fi Models Wi-Fi + Cellular Models <img class="aligncenter wp-image-299712 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Air-640x423.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="423" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Air-640x423.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Air-600x396.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Air-768x507.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Air.jpg 816w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-299714" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Mini.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="589" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Mini.jpg 816w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Mini-435x400.jpg 435w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Mini-768x707.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/New-iPad-Mini-467x430.jpg 467w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (ma